
[1]egotism

   E'GOTISM, n. [L. ego.] Primarily, the practice of too frequently using
   the word I. Hence, a speaking or writing much of one's self;
   self-praise; self-commendation; the act or practice of magnifying one's
   self, or making one's self of importance.

   A deplorable egotism of character.
